            <div type="translation">
                <p>Fasting humbles the body, watching by night purifies the mind, hêsychia produces sorrow (<bibl><ptr target="#Wortley2013"/>,<citedRange> 380</citedRange></bibl>).</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Good condition. A cross with arrays in the angles marks the beginning of the text. The inscription is identified with a saying attributed to Abba Longinus in the Apophegmata Patrum (APanon "Collection")(<bibl><ptr target="#Wortley2013"/>,<citedRange> 380</citedRange></bibl>).</p>  
